description.detailed_html:
Users should provide a visitor with the following methods 

struct Visitor {
  void assign(const Set&);
  void clear();
  void remove(const Set&);
  void add(const Set&);
}
For example: 
SetPatch<SetI32Patch> patch;
patch.remove({20, 30});
patch.add({10, 20});
patch.customVisit(v) will invoke the following methods 
v.add({10, 20});
v.remove({30});

Patch for a Thrift set.

The Patch template parameter must be a Thrift struct with the following fields:

  • optional set<T> assign

  • terse bool clear

  • terse set<T> add

  • terse set<T> remove
